{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01GJ6CirpPdN8hWeVh14a53U","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"ConfigMap created, cluster untouched. Here's what was found and what the script reverts:\n\n**Non-default configuration found:**\n\n| Category | Non-default state |\n|---|---|\n| Vhosts | `/app` (extra; default is `/` only) |\n| Users | `admin [administrator]`, `app-user []` (default is `guest` only) |\n| Permissions | `admin` on `/` and `/app`; `app-user` on `/app` (all `.*`/`.*`/`.*`) |\n| Queues | `app-queue` (classic, durable) in `/app` |\n| Policies | None (already at default) |\n\n**Rollback script logic (`rollback.sh` in ConfigMap `rollback-rehearsal`):**\n1. Re-create the `guest` user with default password `guest` and `administrator` tag\n2. Grant `guest` full permissions on `/`\n3. Delete the `/app` vhost — cascades removal of `app-queue`, its exchanges, bindings, and all `/app`-scoped permissions\n4. Delete `app-user` and `admin`\n\nThe script uses `add_user guest guest || change_password guest guest` so it's idempotent regardless of whether `guest` still exists. The live cluster is unchanged — both `/app` and all users remain in place."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":311,"cache_read_input_tokens":34375,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":311},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e9ed411f-e012-4f4e-a98f-3e370968fa8d","uuid":"4d11593b-9e16-46db-babe-53b8037b5989","request_id":"req_011Cc2hAmNbvjxGtBvA7Ye3D"}
